Halve @brioche buns{2}; toast in a #toaster{} or #skillet{} until golden brown.

Wash and dry produce.

Slice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Season with a pinch of @salt{}.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly slice crosswise into strips.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, toss chicken with half the @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}; sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until chicken is warmed through and cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon} and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}.

Spread cut sides of buns with creamy guacamole. Using #tongs{} or a #slotted spoon{}, fill buns with cheesy chicken; top with tomato. Divide sandos between plates and serve.

> Looking for a delicious, satisfying lunch in just ten minutes? Get ready for the midday repast of your dreams. Close your eyes and picture soft brioche buns slathered with rich guacamole and filled with warm Mexican-spiced chicken layered with melted Monterey Jack cheese and juicy sliced tomato. Nope, it's not a noontime fever dream—it's another delicious lunch idea for which you'll only need to add a napkin (or three!).